      • withNumQueues

        public BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder<T> withNumQueues(int numQueues)
        Requests are sent to queues to be batched. Increasing the number of queues increases parallelism, but may increase the probability of not reaching the maximum buffer size (and therefore increasing the number of batch calls made).
        Parameters:
        numQueues - The number of queues to use. Defaults to BatchRequestsFactory.DEFAULT_NUM_QUEUES
        Returns:
        BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder

      • withNumPollingWorkersPerQueue

        public BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder<T> withNumPollingWorkersPerQueue(int numPollingWorkersPerQueue)
        Sets the number of polling workers per queue. In the case that requests are batched and executed at a much slower rate than the queue is filled, you can add more parallel workers to batch requests.
        Parameters:
        numPollingWorkersPerQueue - Defaults to BatchRequestsFactory.DEFAULT_NUM_WORKERS_PER_QUEUE.
        Returns:
        BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder

      • withBatchSize

        public BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder<T> withBatchSize(int batchSize)
        Parameters:
        batchSize - The maximum number of requests per batch. If the size isn't reached, the worker will wait with the time set by withMaxBufferTimeMs(long). Defaults to BatchRequestsFactory.DEFAULT_MAX_BATCH_SIZE.
        Returns:
        BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder

      • withMaxBufferTimeMs

        public BatchRequestsFactory.BatchRequestsFactoryBuilder<T> withMaxBufferTimeMs(long maxBufferTimeMs)
        Parameters:
        maxBufferTimeMs - The maximum time to wait for a batch to fill to the size set by withBatchSize(int). Defaults to BatchRequestsFactory.DEFAULT_MAX_BUFFER_TIME_MS.
        Returns:
